{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Generate shell autocompletions for swiftly.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/SwiftlyDocs\/documentation\/SwiftlyDocs"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/SwiftlyDocs\/documentation\/SwiftlyDocs\/shell-autocompletion"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Swiftly"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Add shell auto-completions"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swiftly can generate shell autocompletion scripts for your shell to automatically complete subcommands, arguments, options and flags. It does this using the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/apple.github.io\/swift-argument-parser\/documentation\/argumentparser\/installingcompletionscripts\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", which has support for Bash, Z shell, and Fish.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You can ask swiftly to generate the script using the hidden ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--generate-completion-script",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag with the type of shell like this:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swiftly --generate-completion-script <shell>"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "tabs" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "If you have ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "identifier" : "https:\/\/ohmyz.sh\/",
                      "isActive" : true,
                      "type" : "reference"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " installed then this command will install the swiftly completions into the default directory:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "code" : [
                    "swiftly --generate-completion-script zsh > ~\/.oh-my-zsh\/completions\/_swiftly"
                  ],
                  "syntax" : null,
                  "type" : "codeListing"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Otherwise, you’ll need to add a path for completion scripts to your function path, and turn on completion script autoloading. First, add these lines to ~\/.zshrc:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "code" : [
                    "fpath=(~\/.zsh\/completions $fpath)",
                    "autoload -U compinit",
                    "compinit"
                  ],
                  "syntax" : null,
                  "type" : "codeListing"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Next, create the completion directory and add the swiftly completions to it:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "code" : [
                    "mkdir -p ~\/.zsh\/completions && swiftly --generate-completion-script zsh > ~\/.zsh\/completions\/_swiftly"
                  ],
                  "syntax" : null,
                  "type" : "codeListing"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "zsh"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "If you have ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/scop\/bash-completion",
                      "isActive" : true,
                      "type" : "reference"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " installed then this command will install the swiftly completions into the default directory:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "code" : [
                    "swiftly --generate-completion-script bash > swiftly.bash",
                    "# copy swiftly.bash to \/usr\/local\/etc\/bash_completion.d"
                  ],
                  "syntax" : null,
                  "type" : "codeListing"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Without bash-completion create a directory for the completion and generate the script in there:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "code" : [
                    "mkdir -p ~\/.bash_completions && swiftly --generate-completion-script bash > ~\/.bash_completions\/swiftly.bash"
                  ],
                  "syntax" : null,
                  "type" : "codeListing"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Add a line to source that script in your ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "~\/.bash_profile",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " or ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "~\/.bashrc",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " file:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "code" : [
                    "source ~\/.bash_completions\/swiftly.bash"
                  ],
                  "syntax" : null,
                  "type" : "codeListing"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "bash"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Generate the completion script to any path in the environment variable ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "$fish_completion_path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ". Typically this command will generate the script in the right place:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "code" : [
                    "swiftly --generate-completion-script fish > ~\/.config\/fish\/completions\/swiftly.fish"
                  ],
                  "syntax" : null,
                  "type" : "codeListing"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "fish"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "tabNavigator"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Once you have installed the completions you can type out a swiftly command, and press a special key (for example, tab) and the shell will show you the available subcommand, argument, or options to make it easier to assemble a working command-line.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
